            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                <ab><lb n="1"/> <persName type="attested" key="plre:1-serenus3"><name nymRef="Δουλκίτιος">Δουλκῖτι</name></persName>
               <lb n="2"/> <w lemma="εἰκών">εἰκόνα</w> <w lemma="χαλκεότευκτος">χαλκεότευκτον</w> 
                    <lb n="3"/> <w lemma="τίθημι">ἐθήκατο</w> <w lemma="ὅδε">τήνδε</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="Σερῆνος">Ϲερήνῳ</name></persName>
               <lb n="3a"/> <space quantity="1" unit="line"/> 
                 <lb n="4"/> <placeName ref="#lepcis" nymRef="#Λέπτις">Λέπτιϲ</placeName> <w lemma="ἀμείβω">ἀμειβομένη</w> 
                    <lb n="5"/> <persName type="divine" ref="#musa"><name nymRef="Μοῦσα">Μοῦϲαν</name></persName> <w lemma="ἀοιδοπόλος">ἀοιδοπόλον</w>
                </ab></div>
            <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Dulcitius! Leptis dedicò a Sereno questa immagine fatta di bronzo, per ricambiare la (sua) Musa versificatrice</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Dulcitius. This bronze statue Lepcis set up to Serenus, rewarding his verse-making Muse.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Aur. Sempronius Serenus signo Dulcitius: <title>PLRE</title> I, Serenus 3</p>
            </div>
